  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. The area,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A\"><mi>A</mi></math>, of a triangle is given by\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals left parenthesis one half right parenthesis b h\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mi>b</mi><mi>h</mi></math>, where\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> is the length of a base of the triangle and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math> is the corresponding height of the triangle. It's given that a triangle has a base length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> centimeters and a corresponding height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"70\"><mn>70</mn></math> centimeters. Substituting\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> for\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> and\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"70\"><mn>70</mn></math> for\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math> in the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals left parenthesis one half right parenthesis b h\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mi>b</mi><mi>h</mi></math> yields\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals left parenthesis one half right parenthesis left parenthesis 10 right parenthesis left parenthesis 70 right parenthesis\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mn>10</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mn>70</mn></mfenced></math>, or\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper A equals 350\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>350</mn></math>. Therefore, the area, in square centimeters, of the triangle is\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"350\"><mn>350</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the product of the given base and height of the triangle, not its area.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p>Choice D is incorrect. This is the sum of the given base and height of the triangle, not its area.\u00a0</p>",
